The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on December 4, 2020, in honor of National Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day. The proclamation reflects on the attack on Pearl Harbor that occurred on December 7, 1941, where 2,403 Americans, including 68 civilians, lost their lives. It pays tribute to the bravery and sacrifice of the servicemen and women who defended the nation during World War II and highlights the significance of the USS ARIZONA Memorial as a place of remembrance. The proclamation emphasizes the enduring strength of the Pacific Fleet and reaffirms the commitment to never forget the heroes of Pearl Harbor. President Trump encourages Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and he calls for the flag of the United States to be flown at half-staff to honor those who died in service at Pearl Harbor.